title: OKS Stomil Olsztyn
text:
OKS Stomil Olsztyn is a Polish <a href="football%20%28soccer%29">football</a> club based in <a href="Olsztyn">Olsztyn</a>, <a href="Poland">Poland</a>. It was founded on 15 July 1945 as OKS Warmiak. The brightest era of this club was the 1990s when it played in the Polish First League. Between 2004 and 2012 the team was known as OKS 1945 Olsztyn.
Emblem.
The emblem of the club depicts a Great Cormorant.
